comments: Burks (NYK) initiates contact with irving (BKN) by placing a hand to his front and the contact affects his SQBR.
Randle (NYK) makes marginal contact with Irving (BKN) following the screen as he moves toward the basket.
Quickley (NYK) and Jordan (BKN) make incidental foot to foot contact as they move up the floor.
Harden (BKN) and Quickley (NYK) make incidental contact with each other in pursuit of the loose ball.
Irving (BKN) does not beat Randle (NYK) to the spot and is not in a legal guarding position when contact occurs during the drive to the basket.
Burks (NYK) makes contact to Harden's (BKN) body that affects his SQBR.

Quickley (NYK), Bullock (NYK), and Randle (NYK) are all in legal guarding positions when they trap Harden (BKN).  Randle reaches in and gets his hand on the ball and ties up Harden and a held ball is correctly whistled.

Replay review of the foul called on Barrett (NYK) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed successful.  Barrett reaches in across Harris' (BKN shoulder, but makes clean contact with the ball and ties him up.  The whistle occurred when neither team had possession of the ball and a jump ball is administered.

As Randle (NYK) jumps into the air, Irving (BKN) makes contact with the ball, but does not dislodge it and does not cause Randle to return to the floor with possession. Therefore Randle must pass or shoot before returning to the floor. Since he does return to the floor with the ball still in his possession, this is a traveling violation.
Bullock (NYK) commits a take foul on Harden (BKN).
